Vice President Biden met with United Nations and Arab League Joint Special Representative Lakhdar Brahimi and Syrian Opposition Coalition President Moaz al-Khatib in Munich, Germany. They discussed the humanitarian situation in Syria and the regional implications of the crisis. Biden thanked Brahimi for his efforts and pledged continued support from the United States. He praised al-Khatib's leadership and urged him to maintain unity among the opposition, isolate extremists, and be inclusive of various communities in Syria. Biden reiterated the U.S. call for an end to the Assad regime and a transition to a peaceful and democratic Syria. He commended al-Khatib's openness to the possibility of negotiations.